n = int(input())
    rectangles = []
    for i in range(n):
        w, h, c = map(int, input().split())
        rectangles.append((w, h, c))

    pairs = 0
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i+1, n):
            if rectangles[i][0] == rectangles[j][0]: # same widths
                pairs += (rectangles[i][2] * rectangles[j][2]) * (rectangles[i][1] // rectangles[j][1]) # multiply by the number of possible combinations of height and widths that can be created with the given widths and heights. Then multiply by the number of ways to cut the rectangle into pieces with the given heights and widths.

            elif rectangles[i][1] == rectangles[j][1]: # same heights
                pairs += (rectangles[i][2] * rectangles[j][2]) * (rectangles[i][0] // rectangles[j][0])

            else: # different heights and widths
                pairs += (rectangles[i][2] * rectangles[j][2])

    print(pairs)
